    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Rezk%20completion\">[[Rezk completion]]</a> seems like it should be a reflection since it comes with a canonical map forgetting the inherent equality by weakening it to isomorphism and a <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/univalent%20category\">[[univalent category]]</a> seems like it would be a local object wrt maps that just weaken the inherent equality.  However, in that case it's kind of surprising this isn't mentioned on either nLab page.  Is this an oversight or is it not a reflection after all?</p>",
        "id": 506963006,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1742474700
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, univalent (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∞</span></span></span></span>-)categories are reflective in pre-(<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∞</span></span></span></span>-)categories (aka Segal spaces in the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∞</span></span></span></span>-case), and the reflection operation is Rezk completion.</p>",
        "id": 506972064,
